---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = '/tradfi-onchain';
---

<Layout title="HIP-4: Outcome Trading (Prediction Markets) — Hyperliquid">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-24">
    <a href={`${base}/products/hyperliquid`} class="text-zinc-500 text-sm hover:text-cyan-400 transition-colors">← Hyperliquid Overview</a>

    <p class="text-cyan-400 text-sm font-medium tracking-wider uppercase mb-4 mt-8">HIP-4</p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white leading-tight mb-6">
      <span class="lang-en">Outcome Trading</span><span class="lang-zh">結果交易</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-zinc-400 mb-10 leading-relaxed">
      <span class="lang-en">Prediction markets on a real order book, co-designed with Kalshi (CFTC-regulated). Fully collateralized binary contracts — no leverage, no liquidation risk. The killer feature: composability with perps and spot in the same account. Currently on testnet.</span>
      <span class="lang-zh">Prediction market搬上Hyperliquid嘅真order book，由Kalshi（CFTC監管）嘅人一齊設計。買YES買NO，全額抵押，冇leverage、冇爆倉。最正嘅係：計劃同perps、spot共用同一個account同collateral。而家testnet跑緊。</span>
    </p>

    <!-- Status banner -->
    <div class="border border-yellow-800/50 bg-yellow-950/20 rounded-lg p-4 mb-12">
      <p class="text-yellow-400 text-sm font-medium">
        <span class="lang-en">⚠ Status: Testnet (live since Feb 2, 2026). Mainnet date not confirmed. Official docs have not published a complete HIP-4 spec yet. Some details below come from third-party analysis and the Hyperliquid team's public announcements.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">⚠ 而家仲係Testnet（2月2號開始跑）。Mainnet幾時上未知。官方docs仲未出完整spec，以下部分資料嚟自第三方分析同HL團隊嘅公開講法。</span>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-zinc max-w-none text-zinc-400 text-[15px] leading-relaxed space-y-6">

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">What Are Outcome Contracts</span><span class="lang-zh">咩係結果合約</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">Binary financial instruments that settle at <span class="text-white">0</span> or <span class="text-white">1</span> based on whether a real-world event occurs. The price between 0.001 and 0.999 represents the market's implied probability. They trade on Hyperliquid's native order book (CLOB) — the same HyperCore matching engine used for perps and spot.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">簡單講就係二元合約 — 事件發生settle at <span class="text-white">1</span>，唔發生settle at <span class="text-white">0</span>。交易價格喺0.001到0.999之間，反映市場覺得件事發生嘅機率有幾高。跑喺Hyperliquid嘅native order book（CLOB）上面，同perps同spot用同一個HyperCore引擎。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Payoff Structure</span><span class="lang-zh">收益結構</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="border border-green-800/50 bg-green-950/20 rounded-lg p-6">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-medium mb-3"><span class="lang-en">Buy YES at 0.40</span><span class="lang-zh">以0.40買YES</span></p>
          <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm"><span class="lang-en">Deposit: <span class="text-white">0.40 USDH</span></span><span class="lang-zh">存入：<span class="text-white">0.40 USDH</span></span></p>
          <p class="text-green-400 text-sm mt-2"><span class="lang-en">Event occurs → profit <span class="text-white font-bold">0.60</span></span><span class="lang-zh">事件發生 → 賺<span class="text-white font-bold">0.60</span></span></p>
          <p class="text-red-400 text-sm"><span class="lang-en">Event doesn't → lose <span class="text-white font-bold">0.40</span></span><span class="lang-zh">事件唔發生 → 蝕<span class="text-white font-bold">0.40</span></span></p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-red-800/50 bg-red-950/20 rounded-lg p-6">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-medium mb-3"><span class="lang-en">Buy NO at 0.40</span><span class="lang-zh">以0.40買NO</span></p>
          <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm"><span class="lang-en">Deposit: <span class="text-white">0.40 USDH</span></span><span class="lang-zh">存入：<span class="text-white">0.40 USDH</span></span></p>
          <p class="text-green-400 text-sm mt-2"><span class="lang-en">Event doesn't → profit <span class="text-white font-bold">0.60</span></span><span class="lang-zh">事件唔發生 → 賺<span class="text-white font-bold">0.60</span></span></p>
          <p class="text-red-400 text-sm"><span class="lang-en">Event occurs → lose <span class="text-white font-bold">0.40</span></span><span class="lang-zh">事件發生 → 蝕<span class="text-white font-bold">0.40</span></span></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-4">
        <span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">No leverage. No liquidation risk.</span> Fully collateralized — you deposit exactly what you can lose. All settlement in USDH, Hyperliquid's native stablecoin.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">冇槓桿。冇爆倉風險。</span>存幾多最多蝕幾多，就係咁簡單。所有結算用USDH（Hyperliquid自己嘅穩定幣）。</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white font-medium">Margin formula:</span> Long YES at price P requires depositing <code>quantity × P</code>. Long NO (equivalent to short YES) requires <code>quantity × (1 - P)</code>. Mark price is derived from the order book mid-price, subject to standard risk controls.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white font-medium">保證金公式：</span>以價格P買YES需要存入 <code>quantity × P</code>。買NO（等同short YES）需要存入 <code>quantity × (1 - P)</code>。Mark price由order book mid-price衍生，受標準風險控制約束。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Market Lifecycle</span><span class="lang-zh">市場生命週期</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-cyan-950 border border-cyan-800 flex items-center justify-center text-cyan-400 font-bold text-sm flex-shrink-0">1</div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-white font-medium mb-1"><span class="lang-en">Deployment</span><span class="lang-zh">部署</span></p>
            <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm"><span class="lang-en">Builder defines the event schema: title, resolution timestamp, oracle source, authorized oracle updater address. Optional: challenge window for disputes, additional fee share (up to 50%).</span><span class="lang-zh">Builder定義event schema：標題、結算時間戳、oracle來源、授權oracle更新者地址。可選：爭議嘅challenge window、額外fee share（最高50%）。</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-cyan-950 border border-cyan-800 flex items-center justify-center text-cyan-400 font-bold text-sm flex-shrink-0">2</div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-white font-medium mb-1"><span class="lang-en">Opening Auction (~15 min)</span><span class="lang-zh">開盤拍賣（~15分鐘）</span></p>
            <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm"><span class="lang-en">Single-price clearing auction. Orders accumulate without execution. Engine calculates the clearing price that maximizes matched volume. All matched orders fill at the same price. Unfilled orders carry forward to continuous trading.</span><span class="lang-zh">單一價格清算拍賣。Orders累積唔即時執行。引擎計算最大化matched volume嘅clearing price。所有matched orders以相同價格成交。未成交orders帶入連續交易。</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-cyan-950 border border-cyan-800 flex items-center justify-center text-cyan-400 font-bold text-sm flex-shrink-0">3</div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-white font-medium mb-1"><span class="lang-en">Continuous Trading</span><span class="lang-zh">連續交易</span></p>
            <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm"><span class="lang-en">Standard price-time priority order book (CLOB). Limit and market orders. Prices bounded between 0.001 and 0.999.</span><span class="lang-zh">標準price-time priority order book（CLOB）。限價單同市價單。價格限制喺0.001到0.999之間。</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-cyan-950 border border-cyan-800 flex items-center justify-center text-cyan-400 font-bold text-sm flex-shrink-0">4</div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-white font-medium mb-1"><span class="lang-en">Settlement</span><span class="lang-zh">結算</span></p>
            <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm"><span class="lang-en">Oracle posts binary outcome (0 or 1). Trading halts. Open orders cancelled. All positions auto-settle to final PnL in USDH. Optional challenge window before settlement finalized. Market slot recycles for next event.</span><span class="lang-zh">Oracle發布二元結果（0或1）。交易停止。未成交orders取消。所有positions自動結算為最終PnL（USDH）。可選嘅challenge window喺settlement最終確認前。Market slot可recycle用於下一個event。</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Why Not Use Perpetuals for Prediction Markets?</span><span class="lang-zh">點解唔用永續合約做預測市場？</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">HIP-3 perps have a built-in safety mechanism: mark price is <span class="text-white">clamped to max 1% movement per update</span> (every 2.5 seconds minimum). For continuous assets like TSLA or gold, this prevents oracle manipulation. But for binary events, it creates a fatal flaw.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">HIP-3 perps有個安全機制：mark price每次更新<span class="text-white">最多郁1%</span>（最快每2.5秒一次）。對TSLA或黃金呢類連續資產冇問題，防止oracle被人搞。但對binary events就出事。</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white font-medium">Example:</span> "Will Team X win the game?" starts trading at 0.50 (50% probability). Game ends — result is known. Price needs to move from 0.50 to 1.00. With a 1% tick cap, this requires <span class="text-white">~50 price adjustments over ~1 hour</span>. During that entire hour, anyone who knows the result can buy at below 1.00 with zero risk — guaranteed profit. This makes the market fundamentally broken for binary events.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white font-medium">例子：</span>「Team X會唔會贏？」開盤0.50（即50%機率）。比賽完咗，結果已知。價格要從0.50去到1.00。但1% tick cap下，要<span class="text-white">~50次調整、成個鐘</span>。喺呢個鐘入面，任何知道結果嘅人都可以喺低過1.00買入 — 零風險穩賺。成個市場對binary events嚟講根本壞咗。</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">HIP-4 solves this with <span class="text-white">instant binary settlement</span> — price jumps directly from current level to 0 or 1 when the oracle posts the result. No tick-by-tick convergence, no arbitrage window.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">HIP-4點解決？<span class="text-white">即時跳價結算</span> — oracle一出結果，價格直接從當前位跳去0或1。冇慢慢收斂，冇套利窗口。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">No Oracle, No Funding — Price by Trading Alone</span><span class="lang-zh">冇Oracle、冇Funding — 純粹由交易決定價格</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">Unlike standard HIP-3 perps which require continuous oracle feeds and funding rate calculations, Event Perpetuals <span class="text-white">eliminate both</span>. There is no external price feed driving the mark price during trading — the price is determined entirely by trading activity on the order book. The oracle is only used once: at settlement, to post the final binary outcome. This is a fundamentally different design from every other perp product on Hyperliquid.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">普通HIP-3 perps需要不停餵oracle price同計funding rate。Event Perpetuals<span class="text-white">兩樣都唔使</span>。交易期間冇external price feed — 價格完全由order book上面嘅交易活動決定。Oracle得一個用途：結算時出最終結果（0或1）。同Hyperliquid上所有其他perp產品完全唔同嘅設計。</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white font-medium">No funding rate</span> — this matters for position holders. In standard perps, funding payments transfer between longs and shorts every 8 hours, creating a cost for holding positions. HIP-4 outcome contracts have zero funding cost. You can hold a prediction position from deployment to settlement without any carry cost beyond your initial collateral.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white font-medium">冇funding rate</span> — 呢個對持倉者好重要。普通perps每8個鐘有funding payment喺long同short之間轉移，hold position有成本。HIP-4 outcome contracts完全冇funding cost。你可以由deployment hold到settlement，除咗最初嘅collateral之外零額外成本。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">The Kalshi Partnership</span><span class="lang-zh">Kalshi合作關係</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">The HIP-4 proposal was co-authored by an unusually diverse group: <span class="text-white font-medium">Kalshi's head of crypto</span> (CFTC-regulated prediction market), <span class="text-white font-medium">Framework Ventures</span> (crypto VC), <span class="text-white font-medium">Felix Protocol</span> and <span class="text-white font-medium">Asula Labs</span> (DeFi builders). This isn't a single crypto team building in isolation — it's a cross-industry collaboration between regulated TradFi, institutional investors, and DeFi engineers. In March 2026, Kalshi and Hyperliquid announced an official partnership to launch on-chain prediction markets together.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">HIP-4個proposal嘅作者陣容好唔尋常：<span class="text-white font-medium">Kalshi嘅head of crypto</span>（唯一CFTC監管嘅prediction market）、<span class="text-white font-medium">Framework Ventures</span>（crypto VC）、<span class="text-white font-medium">Felix Protocol</span>同<span class="text-white font-medium">Asula Labs</span>（DeFi builder）。唔係一班crypto人自己搞 — 係受監管嘅TradFi、機構投資者、DeFi工程師一齊合作。2026年3月，Kalshi同Hyperliquid正式宣佈合作推鏈上prediction market。</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">This bridges two worlds: Kalshi's regulatory credibility and market design expertise with Hyperliquid's on-chain infrastructure and existing user base. However, regulatory risks remain — in January 2026, a Massachusetts court issued an injunction against Kalshi over sports betting contracts.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">呢個合作接通咗兩個世界：Kalshi嘅監管經驗同市場設計功力，加上Hyperliquid嘅鏈上基建同現有用戶。不過監管風險仲喺度 — 2026年1月Massachusetts法院就sports betting contracts禁咗Kalshi。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Composability — Why This Is Different</span><span class="lang-zh">可組合性 — 點解呢個唔同</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">This is the structural advantage no competitor can match. On Hyperliquid, prediction markets are planned to live in the <span class="text-white">same trading account</span> as perps and spot. Shared collateral, automatic risk offsetting, no cross-platform fund transfers.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">呢個係對手追唔到嘅結構性優勢。Hyperliquid計劃將prediction markets同perps、spot放喺<span class="text-white">同一個trading account</span>入面 — 共用collateral、自動對沖risk、唔使跨平台搬錢。</span>
      </p>

      <div class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-6 mt-4">
        <p class="text-white font-medium mb-3"><span class="lang-en">Example: NVDA Earnings Trade</span><span class="lang-zh">例子：NVDA業績交易</span></p>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm mb-4"><span class="lang-en">You believe NVDA will beat earnings consensus. In one Hyperliquid account, simultaneously:</span><span class="lang-zh">你覺得NVDA業績會beat consensus。喺一個Hyperliquid account入面，同時：</span></p>
        <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
          <p><span class="text-cyan-400">①</span> <span class="lang-en">Buy <span class="text-white">"NVDA beats earnings" YES</span> contract at 0.55</span><span class="lang-zh">以0.55買<span class="text-white">「NVDA beats earnings」YES</span> contract</span></p>
          <p><span class="text-cyan-400">②</span> <span class="lang-en">Long <span class="text-white">NVDA perp</span> 5x to capture post-earnings rally</span><span class="lang-zh">Long <span class="text-white">NVDA perp</span> 5x捕捉業績後反彈</span></p>
          <p><span class="text-cyan-400">③</span> <span class="lang-en">Short <span class="text-white">QQQ perp</span> as a market hedge</span><span class="lang-zh">Short <span class="text-white">QQQ perp</span>做市場hedge</span></p>
        </div>
        <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm mt-4"><span class="lang-en">All three positions share collateral and risk is calculated automatically. Today this requires Polymarket + Hyperliquid + another perp DEX — three platforms, three sets of capital, three withdrawal windows.</span><span class="lang-zh">三個positions共用collateral，risk自動計算。今日做呢個需要Polymarket + Hyperliquid + 另一個perp DEX — 三個平台、三筆資金、三個提款窗口。</span></p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Deployer Economics</span><span class="lang-zh">Deployer經濟模型</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">HIP-4 follows HIP-3's deployer model but with higher requirements, reflecting the added complexity of oracle-dependent event instruments.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">HIP-4沿用HIP-3嘅deployer模型，但要求更高，反映oracle-dependent event instruments嘅額外複雜性。</span>
      </p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto -mx-2 mt-4">
        <table class="w-full text-sm text-left border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
              <th class="py-3 px-2 text-zinc-400 font-medium"><span class="lang-en">Parameter</span><span class="lang-zh">參數</span></th>
              <th class="py-3 px-2 text-zinc-400 font-medium"><span class="lang-en">HIP-3 (Perps)</span><span class="lang-zh">HIP-3（永續）</span></th>
              <th class="py-3 px-2 text-zinc-400 font-medium"><span class="lang-en">HIP-4 (Outcomes)</span><span class="lang-zh">HIP-4（結果）</span></th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-zinc-400">
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
              <td class="py-3 px-2 text-white"><span class="lang-en">HYPE stake</span><span class="lang-zh">HYPE質押</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 px-2">500K (~$25M)</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-2 text-white">1M (~$50M)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
              <td class="py-3 px-2 text-white"><span class="lang-en">Fee share</span><span class="lang-zh">費用份額</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 px-2"><span class="lang-en">Fixed 50%</span><span class="lang-zh">固定50%</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 px-2 text-white"><span class="lang-en">Up to 50% above base</span><span class="lang-zh">基礎費用之上最多50%</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
              <td class="py-3 px-2 text-white"><span class="lang-en">Oracle</span><span class="lang-zh">預言機</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 px-2"><span class="lang-en">Continuous (every 2.5s)</span><span class="lang-zh">連續（每2.5秒）</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 px-2 text-white"><span class="lang-en">Settlement only (once)</span><span class="lang-zh">僅結算時（一次）</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
              <td class="py-3 px-2 text-white"><span class="lang-en">Funding rate</span><span class="lang-zh">資金費率</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 px-2"><span class="lang-en">Yes (continuous)</span><span class="lang-zh">有（連續）</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 px-2 text-white"><span class="lang-en">None</span><span class="lang-zh">無</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
              <td class="py-3 px-2 text-white"><span class="lang-en">Slot recycling</span><span class="lang-zh">Slot回收</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 px-2"><span class="lang-en">Yes (via halt/resume)</span><span class="lang-zh">有（通過暫停/恢復）</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 px-2 text-white"><span class="lang-en">Yes (post-settlement)</span><span class="lang-zh">有（結算後）</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 px-2 text-white"><span class="lang-en">Slashing</span><span class="lang-zh">罰沒</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 px-2"><span class="lang-en">Up to 100%</span><span class="lang-zh">最高100%</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 px-2 text-white"><span class="lang-en">Up to 100% (burned)</span><span class="lang-zh">最高100%（銷毀）</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-4">
        <span class="lang-en">The slot recycling mechanism is critical: one 1M HYPE stake can support an <span class="text-white">unlimited number of rolling markets</span>. A deployer running weekly Fed rate prediction markets amortizes the $50M stake across dozens of events per quarter, dramatically reducing the effective cost per market.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">Slot recycling機制係關鍵：一次1M HYPE stake可以支持<span class="text-white">無限數量嘅rolling markets</span>。一個運行每週Fed利率預測市場嘅deployer可以將$50M stake分攤到每季數十個events，大幅降低每個市場嘅有效成本。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Margin Model: Full Collateralization</span><span class="lang-zh">保證金模型：全額抵押</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">Event Perpetuals enforce strict risk controls that differ fundamentally from standard perps:</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">Event Perpetuals執行嚴格嘅風險控制，同標準perps有根本性嘅不同：</span>
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li><span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">1x isolated margin only</span> — no leverage permitted. This is intentional: prediction markets are probability instruments, not leveraged speculation tools.</span><span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">僅1倍isolated margin</span> — 唔允許leverage。呢個係刻意嘅：prediction markets係概率工具，唔係槓桿投機工具。</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">Full collateralization</span> — buying YES at 0.40 requires depositing exactly 0.40 USDH. Your maximum loss is always your deposit. No margin calls, no liquidations.</span><span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">全額抵押</span> — 以0.40買YES需要存入恰好0.40 USDH。你嘅最大損失永遠係你嘅存款。冇margin call，冇liquidation。</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">Price bands: 0.001 to 0.999</span> — prevents prices from reaching absolute certainty (0 or 1) before settlement. Extreme conviction is capped.</span><span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">價格帶：0.001到0.999</span> — 防止結算前價格達到絕對確定性（0或1）。極端conviction被限制。</span></li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">The Opening Auction (SPCA) — Deep Dive</span><span class="lang-zh">開盤拍賣（SPCA）— 深入分析</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">The Single-Price Clearing Auction is HIP-4's answer to the cold-start problem in prediction markets. Unlike continuous trading where early orders can be front-run or manipulated, the SPCA provides a fair price discovery mechanism:</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">單一價格清算拍賣係HIP-4對prediction markets冷啟動問題嘅解答。唔同於early orders可以被front-run或操縱嘅continuous trading，SPCA提供公平嘅價格發現機制：</span>
      </p>

      <div class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-6 mt-4">
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p><span class="text-cyan-400">①</span> <span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">~15 minutes</span> — orders accumulate in the book without any execution</span><span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">~15分鐘</span> — orders喺book入面累積，冇任何執行</span></p>
          <p><span class="text-cyan-400">②</span> <span class="lang-en">Engine calculates the <span class="text-white">single clearing price</span> that maximizes total matched volume</span><span class="lang-zh">引擎計算最大化total matched volume嘅<span class="text-white">單一clearing price</span></span></p>
          <p><span class="text-cyan-400">③</span> <span class="lang-en">If multiple prices tie on volume, tiebreaker: first <span class="text-white">smallest leftover imbalance</span>, then <span class="text-white">closest to 0.50</span> (neutral probability)</span><span class="lang-zh">如果多個價格嘅成交量相同，tiebreaker：先揀<span class="text-white">剩餘imbalance最細</span>嘅，再揀<span class="text-white">最接近0.50</span>（中性機率）嘅</span></p>
          <p><span class="text-cyan-400">④</span> <span class="lang-en">Orders better than p* fill first. Orders exactly at p* receive <span class="text-white">pro-rata allocation</span> by size. All trades print at uniform p*</span><span class="lang-zh">好過p*嘅orders先fill。剛好at p*嘅orders按size進行<span class="text-white">pro-rata分配</span>。全部以同一個p*成交</span></p>
          <p><span class="text-cyan-400">⑤</span> <span class="lang-en">Unfilled orders carry forward to continuous trading at their original limits</span><span class="lang-zh">未成交orders按原始限價帶入continuous trading</span></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-4">
        <span class="lang-en">This design is borrowed from traditional equity market opens (NYSE, LSE) where batch auctions prevent manipulation during price discovery. It's a sophisticated mechanism rarely seen in DeFi — most prediction markets simply start continuous trading and hope liquidity appears.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">呢個設計借鑑咗傳統股票市場開盤（NYSE、LSE），batch auctions防止價格發現期間嘅操縱。呢個係DeFi中罕見嘅sophisticated機制 — 大部分prediction markets只係開始continuous trading然後希望流動性出現。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Composability — More Examples</span><span class="lang-zh">可組合性 — 更多例子</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">The composability thesis extends far beyond single trades. Here are strategies that become possible only when prediction markets share an account with perps and spot:</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">Composability嘅thesis遠超單一交易。以下係只有當prediction markets同perps同spot共用account時先成為可能嘅策略：</span>
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-4 mt-4">
        <div class="border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/40 rounded-lg p-5">
          <p class="text-white font-medium text-sm mb-2"><span class="lang-en">Fed Rate Macro Hedge</span><span class="lang-zh">Fed利率宏觀對沖</span></p>
          <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs"><span class="lang-en">Buy "Fed cuts 50bps" YES at 0.30. Simultaneously long BTC perp (rate cuts → risk-on) and short DXY perp (rate cuts → dollar weakens). If Fed doesn't cut, prediction loss is offset by DXY gain. All one account.</span><span class="lang-zh">以0.30買「Fed減息50bps」YES。同時long BTC perp（減息→risk-on）同short DXY perp（減息→美元弱）。如果Fed唔減息，prediction loss被DXY gain對沖。全部一個account。</span></p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/40 rounded-lg p-5">
          <p class="text-white font-medium text-sm mb-2"><span class="lang-en">IPO Event Arbitrage</span><span class="lang-zh">IPO事件套利</span></p>
          <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs"><span class="lang-en">Buy "Stripe IPOs before July" YES. Short Stripe pre-IPO perp (via HIP-3). If IPO happens, YES pays out; perp likely moves against you but at known loss. If IPO delayed, YES loses but perp position profits from price decline. Delta-hedged event exposure.</span><span class="lang-zh">買「Stripe七月前IPO」YES。Short Stripe pre-IPO perp（通過HIP-3）。如果IPO發生，YES pay out；perp可能虧但已知損失。如果IPO延遲，YES虧但perp position從價格下跌中獲利。Delta-hedged嘅event exposure。</span></p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/40 rounded-lg p-5">
          <p class="text-white font-medium text-sm mb-2"><span class="lang-en">Geopolitical Tail Hedge</span><span class="lang-zh">地緣政治尾部對沖</span></p>
          <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs"><span class="lang-en">Long oil perp (HIP-3, via trade.xyz). Buy "Middle East escalation" YES as a cheap tail hedge. If escalation happens, oil rallies + YES pays out (double win). If not, YES contract is a small known loss while oil position runs. Classic insurance structure, single account.</span><span class="lang-zh">Long原油perp（HIP-3，via trade.xyz）。買「中東局勢升級」YES作為cheap tail hedge。如果升級發生，油價升+ YES pay out（雙贏）。如果冇，YES contract係小嘅已知損失而油position繼續。經典insurance結構，單一account。</span></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Market Context: Why Prediction Markets Matter Now</span><span class="lang-zh">市場背景：點解prediction markets而家重要</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">The prediction market sector has exploded. Polymarket processed <span class="text-white font-medium">$3.6 billion</span> in trading volume during the 2024 US election alone. ICE (the parent company of NYSE) invested <span class="text-white font-medium">$600 million</span> in Polymarket's parent company. The total addressable market for event-driven trading is massive — every earnings call, every central bank meeting, every election creates tradeable events.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">Prediction market行業已經爆發。Polymarket單喺2024年美國大選期間就處理咗<span class="text-white font-medium">$36億</span>交易量。ICE（NYSE嘅母公司）投資咗<span class="text-white font-medium">$6億</span>到Polymarket嘅母公司。Event-driven trading嘅total addressable market係巨大嘅 — 每次earnings call、每次央行會議、每次選舉都創建可交易嘅events。</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">But existing platforms have structural limitations: Polymarket runs on Polygon with its own CLOB (CTF Exchange) but is a standalone prediction platform with no composability with perps or spot. Kalshi is centralized (no on-chain composability). Neither allows cross-product strategies. HIP-4 positions Hyperliquid to capture this growth by combining prediction markets with its existing perp and spot infrastructure — <span class="text-white">same matching engine, same settlement layer, unified accounts</span>.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">但現有平台有結構性限制：Polymarket運行喺Polygon上，有自己嘅CLOB（CTF Exchange），但係一個獨立嘅prediction platform，同perps或spot冇composability。Kalshi係centralized（冇on-chain composability）。兩者都唔允許cross-product策略。HIP-4令Hyperliquid通過將prediction markets同現有perp同spot infrastructure結合嚟capture呢個增長 — <span class="text-white">同一個matching engine、同一個settlement layer、unified accounts</span>。</span>
      </p>

