      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Risks Specific to HIP-4</span><span class="lang-zh">HIP-4特定風險</span>
      </h2>

      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3">
        <li><span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">Settlement oracle risk</span> — the entire market hinges on a single oracle posting the correct binary outcome. If the oracle is compromised, delayed, or ambiguous, settlement fails. The optional challenge window mitigates this but doesn't eliminate it.</span><span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">結算oracle風險</span> — 整個市場取決於單一oracle發布正確嘅binary outcome。如果oracle被compromised、延遲或模糊，settlement失敗。可選嘅challenge window緩解但唔能消除呢個風險。</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">Event definition ambiguity</span> — "Will BTC hit $100K?" seems clear until you ask: which exchange's price? At what timestamp exactly? Spot or perp? Poorly defined events create disputes that undermine market trust.</span><span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">事件定義模糊性</span> — 「BTC會唔會到$100K？」聽起嚟好清楚，直到你問：邊間交易所嘅價格？確切嘅timestamp係咩？現貨定perp？定義不清嘅events產生爭議，損害市場信任。</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">Regulatory uncertainty</span> — Massachusetts issued an injunction against Kalshi over sports betting contracts (Jan 2026). CFTC's stance on broader event contracts remains unclear. The Kalshi partnership provides regulatory expertise but not immunity.</span><span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">監管不確定性</span> — Massachusetts就sports betting contracts對Kalshi發出禁令（2026年1月）。CFTC對更廣泛event contracts嘅立場仍不明確。Kalshi合作提供監管專業知識但唔係免疫。</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">Liquidity risk</span> — prediction markets suffer from severe liquidity concentration around popular events and near-zero liquidity for niche events. Without HLP backstop (same as HIP-3), deployers must solve this independently.</span><span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">流動性風險</span> — prediction markets受到嚴重嘅流動���集中影響：熱門events有流動性，niche events幾乎零流動性。冇HLP backstop（同HIP-3一樣），deployers必須獨立解決。</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">Bounded payoff limits LP appetite</span> — outcome contracts have capped upside (max payout = 1). This is fundamentally less attractive for LPs compared to perpetuals which have uncapped fee revenue from continuous funding rates. Market-making in prediction markets requires different economics.</span><span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">有上限嘅payoff限制LP參與意欲</span> — outcome contracts嘅upside有cap（最大payout = 1）。同有uncapped fee revenue（嚟自continuous funding rates）嘅perpetuals相比，對LP嚟講吸引力根本唔同。Prediction market嘅做市需要唔同嘅economic model。</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">Composability is planned, not guaranteed</span> — shared accounts between prediction markets, perps, and spot are described in third-party analysis but <span class="text-white">not yet confirmed in official Hyperliquid documentation</span>. This is the strongest selling point but also the most uncertain.</span><span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">Composability係計劃中而非保證</span> — prediction markets、perps同spot之間嘅shared accounts喺第三方分析中描述但<span class="text-white">仲未喺官方Hyperliquid文檔中確認</span>。呢個係最強嘅賣點但都係最不確定嘅。</span></li>
      </ul>

